article.headline: East Tenn. St. 73, Elon University 58
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 21 points as East Tennessee State defeated Elon 73-58 on Saturday for the Buccaneers' 13th straight victory. Elon (9-15, 5-7 Southern Conference ) scored first on a couple of free throws by Jackson Atoyebi, but East Tennessee State (21-4, 13-0) took the lead for good 5-2 on a basket by Ben Rhoda and a 3-pointer by Smith. The Buccaneers slowly pulled away to lead 44-29 at halftime. Elon cut it to 48-41 with 14:07 left in the game, but the Bucaneers pulled away to lead by as much as 70-58 with 2:33 left. James Anthony had 13 points for East Tennessee State and Zakee Wadood had 10. Jackson Atoyebi led Elon with 17 points and Matt Nowlin had 11.
